what pulsars were. Pulsars, as you may know,

00:11:11.379 --> 00:11:17.160
when a star goes supernova, it collapses.
And all of that rotational inertia is preserved.

00:11:17.160 --> 00:11:22.600
And as it collapses down into a neutron star,
it's spinning. So all the spin that the sun

00:11:22.600 --> 00:11:26.970
had is greatly accelerated like a figure skater
bringing in her arms.

00:11:26.970 --> 00:11:32.050
And so it's spinning quite fast. And it shoots
out this jet of x-rays and gamma rays, which

00:11:32.050 --> 00:11:36.600
is also not completely understood how or why
they shoot out these jets. But each time that

00:11:36.600 --> 00:11:41.170
jet spins by us, and if we're on the same
plane, we hear a click like that. And that's

00:11:41.170 --> 00:11:45.399
